# high-blast path policy (default-deny) — T03 blast router.
#
# A change is auto-merge-eligible (low-blast) ONLY if its REAL git diff is readable,
# non-empty, and NO changed path matches any glob below. A match → high-blast → open a
# PR for a human, never auto-merge to integration. Classify-fail / empty-diff /
# read-error also fall to high-blast (deny by default). Every changed path is matched,
# including BOTH sides of a rename and deleted paths.
#
# Glob: `**` matches across directory separators, `*` within one path segment,
# `?` one non-separator char. A leading `**/` also matches a top-level path.

# --- infra / deploy / ops: irreversible or out-of-band blast ---
**/migrations/**
**/migration/**
**/.github/**
**/launchd/**
**/*.plist
**/Dockerfile
**/docker-compose*.yml
**/*.tf
**/*.tfvars

# --- secrets / credentials: never auto-land ---
**/secrets/**
**/*.env
**/.env*
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/id_rsa*

# --- dependency / supply-chain surface ---
**/package.json
**/package-lock.json
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/yarn.lock
**/Cargo.toml
**/Cargo.lock
**/requirements*.txt
**/pyproject.toml

# --- the autonomy harness itself: editing the driver is a meta decision (human-gate) ---
scripts/pandastack-drive
scripts/drive-cron.py
scripts/agent-worker
scripts/pslib.py
config/high-blast-paths
